In the year 1970 Temin and Baltimore proved the existence of the transfer of genetic 
information from an RNA virus to a DNA of a host cell; with the help of the reverse 
transcriptase enzyme (it synthesizes DNA according to the RNA matrix). This altered the 
central dogma of molecular (Fig. 62). 

 
 
 
 
 
