 After finishing blotting we need to prepare the probe. The probe is a single-stranded, 
radioactively or chemically labeled DNA (in some case a RNA) with a known sequence of 
nitrogen bases. During radioactive labeling nucleotides which contain a radioactive isotope, 
usually 32P or 35S, are integrated into the sequence of the probe. During non-radioactive 
